            "discussion": "<p>Expect the warmest temperatures in almost 2 weeks and enough sun to maintain the threat of wet loose avalanches. You may be able to trigger avalanches and they could release naturally from overhead terrain. Avalanches could gouge into deeper layers of snow, becoming big enough to bury or kill you.</p>\n<p>Give yourself plenty of options of lower angle or shaded terrain. Make sure you have plenty of time to be off of steep slopes before they get warm and weak. Take note of warming and wetting at the snow surface or previously supportable crusts melting and becoming weak. If you observe signs of instability like rollerballs, pinwheels, or very small avalanches, move to more shaded or lower angle slopes.</p>",
